What degree of formalization and centralization does ABC have?

ABC Corp. has a high degree of formalization and centralization.

Formalization refers to the level of standardization and documentation of procedures and processes within an organization. In ABC Corp., the company has highly documented procedures and the job description of every employee is carefully crafted and remains fixed. This indicates that the company has a high level of formalization, as there is a clear set of rules and procedures that employees are expected to follow.

Centralization refers to the degree to which decision-making authority is concentrated at the top levels of an organization. In ABC Corp., the company has a CEO to whom everyone reports through a few managers, and low-level employees have little decision-making authority. This indicates that the company has a high degree of centralization, as decision-making power is concentrated at the top levels of the organization.

